<subSubSection id="D9AD6543FFBAFFA3D7EB889DFAF1FB79" box="[755,1371,1158,1184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="910836C8FFBAFFA3D7EB889DFAF1FB79" blockId="6.[151,1437,1158,1761]" box="[755,1371,1158,1184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Red Devil; Mojarra Picuda, Diablo Rojo (
<figureCitation id="098C2A4DFFBAFFA3D1D0889DFAE5FB79" box="[1224,1359,1158,1184]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[151,198,1474,1498]" captionTargetBox="[341,1245,179,1448]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[341,1246,179,1448]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 2. New country records. (A) Amphilophus labiatus, specimen captured in the Río San Juan, San Carlos, Alajuela (ca 10.89057, -84.26540), at ca 26 m.a.s.l., in November 2020, by an anonymous angler. (B) Amphilophus labiatus, specimen captured in the Río Sapoá, La Cruz, Guanacaste (11.21815, -85.60819), at 8 m.a.s.l., on January 19, 1967, by William Bussing and Myrna López (UCR 0122-014). (C) Anchovia clupeoides, specimen captured in the Río Pacuare, near the mouth of the river, Siquirres, Limón (10.21952, -83.28254), at 8 m.a.s.l., on November 17, 2004, by Jorge Picado (UCR 2840-005). (D) Colossoma macropomum, specimen captured in the Río Bebedero, Portones de Taboga, Bebedero, Cañas, Guanacaste, Costa Rica (10.36978, -85.19772), at 10 m.a.s.l., on March 27, 2020, by Javier Blandon. (E) Colossoma macropomum, specimen captured in the Río Bebedero, Altamira, Cañas, Guanacaste, Costa Rica (10.35378, -85.20408), at 18 m.a.s.l., on April 30, 2021, by Agustin Guzman. (F) Gobioides peruanus being depredated by the Bare-throated Tiger Heron (Trigrisoma mexicanum Swainson, 1834), photo captured in the Quebrada Bomba Vieja (Barranca river basin), near the mouth of the Río Barranca, El Roble, Puntarenas (9.96228, -84.73493), at 6 m.a.s.l., on January 6, 2021, by Beto Guido Méndez (Bird watcher guide/Naturalist). (G) Hypostomus cf. niceforoi, specimens captured in the Humedal Caño Negro, Los Chiles, Alajuela (ca 10.89081, -84.79415), at ca 33 m.a.s.l., on May 11-16, 2016, by Didiher Chacón-Chaverri. (H) Lutjanus purpureus, specimen captured in the Quebrada Hone Creek/Río Carbón, Talamanca, Limón (9.67153, -82.79047), at 12 m.a.s.l., on October 6, 2007, by Maribel Mafla et al. (UCR 2751-001). (I) Lutjanus purpureus, specimen captured in the Río Moín, at the Puerto Fluvial JAPDEVA, Limón (09.99745, -83.08077), at 7 m.a.s.l., on December 14, 2006, by Karina Rodríguez (UCR 2761-003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5800636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5800636/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs. 2A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9AD6543FFBAFFA3D5DF88B1FD51FA19" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="910836C8FFBAFFA3D5DF88B1FD51FA19" blockId="6.[151,1437,1158,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBAFFA3D5DF88B1FEEEFB1D" bold="true" box="[199,324,1194,1220]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species differs from the other species of the family occurring in the freshwaters of the country by the following combination of characters: teeth pointed, conical, without second cusp on premaxillary and mandibular teeth of the 1st series; lips thick and large, the lower lip continuous, without a frenum (see 
<bibRefCitation id="F5264B39FFBAFFA3D05A88E9FF79FAE9" author="Bussing, W. A." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refId="ref63850" refString="Bussing, W. A. (1998). Freshwater fishes of Costa Rica. Editorial Universidad de Costa Rica, San Jose, Costa Rica, 468 pp." type="book" year="1998">Bussing 1998</bibRefCitation>
); cheek scale series 4–5 (see 
<bibRefCitation id="F5264B39FFBAFFA3D70F8903FD73FAE8" author="Rican, O. &amp; Pialek, L. &amp; Dragova, K. &amp; Novak, J." box="[535,729,1302,1331]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 102" refId="ref66138" refString="Rican, O., Pialek, L., Dragova, K. &amp; Novak, J. (2016) Diversity and evolution of the Middle American cichlid fishes (Teleostei: Cichlidae) with revised classification. Vertebrate Zoology, 66 (1), 1 - 102." type="journal article" year="2016">
Říčan 
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBAFFA3D746890CFD3CFAE9" box="[606,662,1302,1328]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
); dorsal fin spines 16–17; and anal fin spines 6–7. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFBAFFA3D58F8920FEBAFA8D" baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[151,272,1338,1365]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Amphilophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="labiatus">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBAFFA3D58F8920FEBAFA8D" box="[151,272,1338,1365]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. labiatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the closely related 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFBAFFA3D76A8921FB9DFA8C" authority="(Gunther, 1864)" baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[626,1079,1338,1365]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Amphilophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="citrinellus">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBAFFA3D76A8921FCD4FA8D" box="[626,894,1338,1364]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Amphilophus citrinellus</emphasis>
(Günther, 1864)
</taxonomicName>
by having a larger (37.8–39.5% of Standard Length – SL; vs. 35.0–35.6% of SL) and thinner (Head Depth – HD = 79.9–90.9% of Head Length – HL; vs. HD = 111.5–118.9 of HL) head and a larger (42.8–43.4% of HL; vs. 40.4–41.9% of HL) snout. See 
<bibRefCitation id="F5264B39FFBAFFA3D05B8999FECCFA19" author="Stauffer Jr., J. R. &amp; McKaye, K. R." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref66696" refString="Stauffer Jr., J. R. &amp; McKaye, K. R. (2002) Descriptions of three new species of cichlid fishes (Teleostei: Cichlidae) from Lake Xiloa, Nicaragua. Cuadernos de Investigacion de la Universidad de Centro America, 12, 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="2002">Stauffer &amp; McKaye (2002)</bibRefCitation>
for a detailed comparative analysis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9AD6543FFBAFFA3D61989BDFD9AF9F4" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="910836C8FFBAFFA3D61989BDFD9AF9F4" blockId="6.[151,1437,1158,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBAFFA3D61989BDFC43FA19" bold="true" box="[769,1001,1446,1472]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Basis of the record:</emphasis>
<collectionCode id="F7A6AE0DFFBAFFA3D6F789BDFBA8FA19" box="[1007,1026,1446,1472]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A</collectionCode>
single specimen was captured in the 
<collectingRegion id="5373F82AFFBAFFA3D58F89D1FE89FA3C" box="[151,291,1482,1509]" country="Nicaragua" name="Rio San Juan" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">río San Juan</collectingRegion>
, San Carlos, Alajuela (
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBAFFA3D73889D0FD90FA3D" box="[544,570,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">ca</emphasis>
<geoCoordinate id="F483500FFFBAFFA3D75989D1FD07FA3C" box="[577,685,1482,1509]" degrees="10.89057" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" precision="1" value="10.89057">10.89057</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="F483500FFFBAFFA3D7AF89D1FC84FA3C" box="[695,814,1482,1509]" degrees="84.26540" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" precision="1" value="-84.2654">-84.26540</geoCoordinate>
), at 
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBAFFA3D64289D0FCDEFA3D" box="[858,884,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">ca</emphasis>
<specimenCount id="87B1FD41FFBAFFA3D66389D1FC14FA3D" box="[891,958,1482,1508]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="generic">
<quantity id="564F9B2DFFBAFFA3D66389D1FC10FA3D" box="[891,954,1482,1508]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="m" value="26.0">26 m</quantity>
