</specimenCount>
a.s.l., in 
<date id="E5091008FFBAFFA3D10F89D1FB64FA3D" box="[1047,1230,1482,1508]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2020-11">November 2020</date>
, by an anonymous angler. Additional specimens, identified as 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFBAFFA3D76789F4FD53F9D1" baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[639,761,1518,1545]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Amphilophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="labiatus">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBAFFA3D76789F4FD53F9D1" box="[639,761,1518,1545]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. labiatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are deposited at the fish collection of the UCR (0122-014, 0240-001, 0429-002 and 0804-005).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9AD6543FFBAFFA3D72F8A09FBBBF939" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="910836C8FFBAFFA3D72F8A09FBBBF939" blockId="6.[151,1437,1158,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBAFFA3D72F8A09FD07F9F5" bold="true" box="[567,685,1554,1580]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks:</emphasis>
Previous records in the country of this species have been assigned to the closely related 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFBAFFA3D4908A2CFDB0F989" baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[392,538,1590,1617]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Amphilophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="citrinellus">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBAFFA3D4908A2CFDB0F989" box="[392,538,1590,1617]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. citrinellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species prefers lacustrine environments, being more abundant in the Lake 
<collectingCountry id="E9A07658FFBAFFA3D58F8A41FEA4F9AD" box="[151,270,1626,1652]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
; it has rarely been captured in lotic environments (
<bibRefCitation id="F5264B39FFBAFFA3D65A8A41FC4BF9AD" author="Bussing, W. A." box="[834,993,1626,1652]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refId="ref63850" refString="Bussing, W. A. (1998). Freshwater fishes of Costa Rica. Editorial Universidad de Costa Rica, San Jose, Costa Rica, 468 pp." type="book" year="1998">Bussing 1998</bibRefCitation>
). As in 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFBAFFA3D12D8A40FB6CF9AD" baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[1077,1222,1626,1653]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Amphilophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="citrinellus">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBAFFA3D12D8A40FB6CF9AD" box="[1077,1222,1626,1653]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. citrinellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a polychromatism has been described for this species; with a cryptic form (grey or brown with dark bars or spots; 
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBAFFA3D1F78A64FABBF941" box="[1263,1297,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">i.e.</emphasis>
, the normal morph) and a conspicuous form (which lacks melanophores, resulting in brightly red, orange, or yellowish colored fish; 
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBAFFA3D5C88ADCFF59F939" box="[208,243,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">i.e.</emphasis>
, the gold morph), both occurring naturally (
<bibRefCitation id="F5264B39FFBAFFA3D7F88ADDFBAFF939" author="Barluenga, M. &amp; Meyer, A." box="[736,1029,1734,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="2061 - 2076" refId="ref63309" refString="Barluenga, M. &amp; Meyer, A. (2004) The Midas cichlid species complex: incipient sympatric speciation in Nicaraguan cichlid fishes? Molecular Ecology, 13 (7), 2061 - 2076. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 294 X. 2004.02211. x" type="journal article" year="2004">Barluenga &amp; Meyer 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
